# Excellence — Enterprise-Grade Completeness

**Hivork = professional product.** Not minimal MVP fields/UI/flows.

Before ANY table, form, flow, page, or backend logic → read:
`docs/09-development/EXCELLENCE-STANDARDS.md`

## Database (every table)

Base fields: `id`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `createdById`, `updatedById`, `deletedAt`, `deletedById`, `version` (financial), `metadata` JSON  
Tenant tables: `tenantId` + indexes on FKs and `(tenantId, status)`  
Soft delete only — no hard delete — `SOFT-DELETE-POLICY.md`

## Backend (every use case)

Permission + module + data scope + audit + validation + edge cases (409 duplicate, version conflict, plan limits)  
List APIs: cursor pagination, sort, filter, search

## Forms (every form)

Label, placeholder, help, fa validation, loading, server errors, unsaved warning, a11y, RTL, mobile input types

## Pages (every page)

Breadcrumb, title, actions, filters, skeleton/empty/error states, no permission state

## Flows (every flow)

Document: entry, steps, errors, exit, recovery. Multi-step = progress + back + summary

## Rule

If a field/state/UX path is reasonable for pro users → **include it** unless documented out of scope.

Do NOT ship happy-path-only UI or bare-minimum schemas.

